The dark blue curve is maintain a near constant slope, representing that at the 
lowest crowd density there were no blockages. Either the purple or the light
blue curve, presents a sharp slope (at 8th and 29th individual, respectively) 
which is a graphical representation of a door blockage. Another way to see the blockages is through the time void between two 
egresses, which is presented in Figures [#graf-70] and [#graf-210].

~ Figure { #graf-70; caption: "Time void between egresses for 70 individuals experiment."}
