On Figure [#graf-210] the graphic shows eight times the one second intervals when
none individual had gotten out. That means, people were right in front
of the door, striving to egress but blocking one against other. Even less populated environment
can develop blockages longer than one second, as it is seemed right before
the escape of the 23th individual on Figure [#graf-70].

